49. octava: sc. hora. The ninth was usua13 to dine at an earlier hour was regarded as luxurious (tempestivum convivium). Of. Hor. Sat. 11, 8, 3 de medio potare die. Uarius Priscus was in 99-100 Aa). tried and convicted of extortion practised during his proconsulship in Africa. Pliny, Ep. 11, 11, gives a full account of the case, in which he and Cornelius Tacitus acted sor the injured province. Marius was heavily fined and banished (relegatus), but retained most of his ill-gotten gains, His grasping policy in Africa is referred to again in 8, 120.
